<title>FRANCE: Franco-German-British-Italian arms agency created.</title>
<headline>Franco-German-British-Italian arms agency created.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-11-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>The defence ministers of France, Germany, Britain and Italy signed an accord in Strasbourg, eastern France, on Tuesday creating a new joint arms agency, the French defence ministry said.</p>
<p>The new body, to be called &quot;Organisation for Joint Cooperation in Armaments (OCCAR)&quot; is based on existing Franco-German arms programmes to which Britain and Italy have asked to be associated, the ministry said in a statement.</p>
<p>No specific arms programmes were mentioned but specialists said the development of a new common infantry fighting vehicle would be a main project for the agency.</p>
<p>The body, which is expected to launch research programmes, was created as part of joint efforts to form a continent-wide arms agency, the ministry said.</p>
